The paper focuses on developing a model for Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves understanding the visual scene in an image and modeling inter-object relations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a graph attention mechanism to encode relations between objects, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its model on VQA datasets, which involves information retrieval and reasoning, indicating that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
